rComments: Dr. Morris is awesome! He's been teaching for ever and it shows. He really knows his stuff and he's super interested. He works really hard to ensure your understanding. Tends to get off topic but it always results in something funny. I'm a biology major and I've never had a bio prof like this. Not your usual stuffy, fact reciting prof.

Occasionally loses his trail of thought, and often posts ancient handwritten notes from the 60s that are difficult to read. However, his verbal explanations are well done and he is extremely helpful and  a very, very nice person. He also keeps you amused in class. His tests are unconventional, in that they involve no MCQ but drawing and labeling.
